biography_text: McMORRIS RODGERS, Cathy, a Representative from Washington; born in Salem, Marion County, Oreg., May 22, 1969; graduated from Kettle Falls High School, Kettle Falls, Wash., 1986; B.A., Pensacola Christian College, Pensacola, Fla., 1990; M.B.A., University of Washington, Seattle, Wash., 2002; family orchard business; member of the Washington state house of representatives, 1994-2004, minority leader, 2002-2003; elected as a Republican to the One Hundred Ninth and to the six succeeding Congresses (January 3, 2005-present); chair, House Republican Conference (One Hundred Thirteenth through One Hundred Fifteenth Congresses).
